--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LIMB - Lithesome Interactive Media Builder -  $Id$
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/limb

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 !!!WARNING!!!
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This  is  the  pre-alfa of  the  public  release of  LIMB  based  project. These
instructions contain ***only*** necessary information on how to get LIMB based project
working.
You're strongly required to be able to configure Apache, MySQL.
If you're stuck and need help, please feel free to contact the developers over email: 
limb@0x00.ru

! This package doesn't contains tests. Contact developers in case you need tests.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OS : OS independent

Web Server: Apache  1.3+ (configured  with  AllowOverride  All) with php istalled as
a module(important!)

Development Environment: PHP 4.2+  

Preferred Database: MySQL 4.0+ 
(LIMB will work on 3.23+ with InnoDB support, however LIMB uses full text search 
capabilities of 4.0+ version, hence no search support below 4.0)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	SETUP PROJECT 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.	Unpack downloaded archive
2.	Edit project settings in setup_custom.php
3.	Dump data base structure and initial data from sql.sql that you can find 
	in /YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/init/ directory

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	SETUP APACHE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You need to write an alias for shared folder in the apache project virtual host 
section:
Alias /shared 		/YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/limb/shared/

You may skip this step by simply copying /YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/limb/shared/ contents
to /YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/shared/ folder.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	SETTING PERMISSIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Your PHP installation will need write access to a 'var' directory in the project folder.
Usually this directory contains several subfolders: 'compiled', 'cache', 'media', 'log'. 
Also if you want to run tests you will have to set write permissions to 'var' in 
'YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/tests/' folder.
After installation use /root/admin address to get access to the administration zone.
To log in 'admin' as a login and 'test' as a password.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	config.ini
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Every project has config.ini file in /core/settings folder

By default it contains only one valuable parameter:
force_compile = 1

This parameter forces the WACT template engine to recompile requested template every time 
it is requested.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 TEMPLATE FILE NAME RESOLVING 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Templates can be found in YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/design/main/templates/
folder or in YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/limb/design/default/templates/ folder.

Templating engine first looks up the requested template in
YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/design/main/templates/ 
if not found, it tries
YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER/limb/design/default/templates/.